What is CFD
Dahsboards in jira

Swimlanes in Jira
  •	Used to group issues visually on boards
  •	By assignee
  •	By work type
  •	By status
Cumulative flow diagram 
  •	A chart that shows how work items are moved across states over time
  •	What is displays
      o	X – axis: time
      o	Y- axis: number of issues
      o	Coloured bands: workflow states

JQL
  •	Jira Query Language (JQL) is powerful, text-based language used to create complex search queries to find and filter issues within the Jira
  JQL (Jira Query Language) filters are powerful search queries used in Jira to find specific work items (issues) based on criteria like project,
  status, assignee, and custom fields, functioning like a search engine to narrow down results for better management, dashboards, and integrations.

  Filters are saved JQL searches, allowing reuse and sharing, and use fields, operators (like =, !=, ~), and values, combined with keywords like AND,
  OR, and ORDER BY, to create complex, custom views of your Jira data. 
  •	Example: project = ABC AND status = "In Progress"

What is dashboard
  •	A Jira Dashboard is a single screen that shows important project information using gadgets (small widgets).
  •	Personal Dashboard
    o	Used by individual users to track their own work.
    o	Example: Developer’s Personal Dashboard
    o	Issues assigned to me
    o	Bugs I need to fix today
    o	Tasks due this week
    o	My sprint progress
  •	Team Dashboard
    o	Used by entire teams (Scrum team, QA team, Managers).
    o	Example: Scrum Team Dashboard
    o	Sprint progress
    o	Remaining work
    o	Blocked issues
    o	Team velocity
  •	Everyone sees the same result and reduce daily status meetings
  •	What is a Gadget?
    o	A gadget displays specific data like issue lists, charts, or progress.
  •	Example: filter result gadget, pie chart gadget etc
  •	Burndown chart
    o	It shows remaining work vs time in a sprint


